title: cinnamon-lemon cookies
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream together sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking powder, lemon peel and salt.
Cover and refrigerate 2 hours until firm.
Shape dough into small balls about 3/4-inch in diameter.
Roll in cinnamon-sugar to coat.
Place cookies 1-inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Cool slightly before your remove from baking sheets.

title: apple streusel
directions: Grease sides and bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan.
Arrange apples in pan, overlapping rows.
Stir together the white sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over apples.
Stir together the brown sugar and flour; cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Pat down to a smooth surface.
Bake for 30 minutes at 425°, or until apples are tender.

title: slush punch
directions: Boil water and sugar until sugar is dissolved.
When cooled, add pineapple juice, pineapple and bananas.
Put in freezer for 1 or 2 hours before you want to use.
Just before serving, add 2 liter 7-Up.
This should be thick like a slush.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Mix well and refrigerate overnight.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix and bake
cake in a 12 x 18-inch sheet cake pan for 20 minutes.
(It
will
be thin.) Beat pudding with milk.
Add cream cheese.
Add
Cool Whip.
Chill and spread on cake.
Add pineapple, then
coconut,
then
cherries and last nuts.
This cake freezes well and stays moist a long time.
Keep refrigerated.

title: mennet's coffee cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients
and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients; mix.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake for 25 or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie soup(a real diet soup)
directions: Place ingredients in large soup pot.
With a whole head of cabbage, use 1 pound carrots, 1 onion, 1/4 bunch celery, one pepper and several tomatoes or 1 can tomatoes.
Add water to cover.
Add salt and pepper and whatever you like to season soup with.
Cook at simmer for 1 hour.
Taste and season more if necessary.
Cool and store in refrigerator or freezer.
Carrots will get mushy in freezer but palatable.
Eat as much as you like. Very low calorie.
Good for heart patients.
Leave out pepper. It is also gassy for some.
You can add potatoes for a more robust soup and other veggies like peas, squash, turnips and so on.
Add red or pinto beans, cooked, too.
Add bits of macaroni and parsley.
Basic soup is good.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Mix and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350 for 1/2 hour.
Serve with Devonshire Toast Rounds.

title: zucchini orange salad
directions: In a large bowl, toss zucchini, onion and celery.
Cover with boiling water; let stand 1 hour.
Drain.
Add beans and oranges. Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil; boil for 1 minute.
Pour over salad; cover and refrigerate 24 hours before serving.

title: apple salad
directions: Sift together flour and sugar.
Mix in pineapple.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Add butter and cool.
Mix with apples and put in dish.
Pat Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: aunt dorothy's ice cream pie
directions: Put pudding, milk and ice cream in a bowl; mix thoroughly for 2 minutes.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: fettucine alfredo
directions: Cook fettucine.
Steam vegetables.
Mix all ingredients (vegetables and cooked fettucine) together.
Warm at 250° in oven for 20 minutes.

title: *caramel nut acorns
directions: Stir brown sugar, vanilla and pecans into melted butter or margarine.
Add sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Shape in round balls.
Flatten one side by pressing on ungreased cookie sheet.
Pinch top to a point to resemble an acorn.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy italian dressing
directions: Beat oil into mayonnaise, add all other ingredients. Chill before serving. Store in refrigerator.

title: stir-fry veggies
directions: Put in large frypan with 2 tablespoons oil.
Cook on low to medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Salt to taste.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream together sugars, eggs and margarine. Add soda, vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt. Mix well. Stir in oats and Rice Krispies. Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: bull chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugars, vanilla and eggs together.
Add rest of ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cream peas
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter. Whisk in milk (don't boil). Whisk flour until medium thickness consistency. Add seasoning and drained peas. Let set for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop chipped beef in blender.
Mix with cream cheese and salad dressing until smooth.
Form into a ball.
Roll in pecans until covered.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the green beans and mushroom soup with 1/2 of the cheese. Sprinkle the remaining cheese on top of the mixture.
Heat at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until the mixture is hot.
Add the fried onions to the top of hot mixture, covering it; the amount may be varied according to taste.
Heat 5 to 7 more minutes.

title: microwave mexican dip and chips
directions: Mix together salsa and cheeses.
Microwave for four minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve with chips.

title: golden yellow corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
While oven is preheating, place 1/4 cup margarine in 10-inch skillet and melt in oven.

title: sausage skillet
directions: Rinse sauerkraut.
In heavy medium size pan, heat bacon drippings and add onion to saute.
Add remaining ingredients except sausage.
Cover and cook slowly for 15 minutes or until apple slices are soft.
Add quartered sausage and continue slowly cooking, covered, until sausage is heated through.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients except the flour.
Blend well.
Stir in flour.
Chill.
Preheat oven to 375°.
On lightly floured surface, roll out dough, a third at a time, about 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place 1-inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 7 to 10 minutes until golden brown.
Cool and frost, if desired.
Delicious!

title: baked corn
directions: Saute onion and pepper until soft in oleo.
Combine all ingredients and pour into small casserole.
Bake at 350° until set and light brown.
We like to put dollops of sour cream on top before putting in the oven.

title: flying farmer chicken salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Toss in remaining ingredients.
Let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift again with baking powder and salt.
Cut in butter and cheese with 2 knives.
Add milk; mix lightly.
Drop by teaspoon on well-oiled baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 450° for 12 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix together with your fingers.
Roll into bite size.
Bake on a cookie sheet in 300° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken, or use skinned deboned chicken. Combine cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Beat egg and water together.
Dip chicken pieces in egg mixture, then coat with crumb mixture.
Place chicken pieces in baking pan that has been coated with Pam cooking spray.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Uncover last five or ten minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dandelion dressing
directions: Fry little pieces of bacon.
Beat egg in vegetable dish.
Beat together with salad dressing, vinegar and sugar.
Stir all together.
Fill dish with cold water up to about 1 1/2 inches of dish.
Stir all around.
Pour in frypan on top of bacon.
Make it hot and bubbly, then add your clean, washed dandelion.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix; set 1 hour.
Shake frequently.
Pour over washed and cut vegetables; set 2 hours.
Suggested vegetables: broccoli, mushrooms, carrots, onions, etc.

title: pop eye
directions: Mix by hand; add more flour, if needed, so it's not too sticky.
Roll out thinly; cut into squares and let dry.
Cook about 20 minutes until tender in broth.

title: lemon ginger chiffon pie
directions: Combine crust ingredients; chill as pie shell.

title: punch
directions: Mix and let stand overnight.
When ready to serve, pour mix into a large punch bowl, then add 2 quarts of cold ginger ale by pouring down side of bowl to preserve carbonation.
Makes 25 (5 ounce) cups.

title: beat and eat frosting
directions: Combine egg white, sugar and cream of tartar in mixing bowl. Add boiling water and beat until thick and fluffy. Add vanilla. Frosts a 9-inch cake.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine crushed wafers with butter and cinnamon.
Press into bottom and sides of a 10-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.
Melt the semi-sweet chocolate in top of double boiler over warm water. Beat softened cream cheese in large mixer bowl until fluffy and smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar, then eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add melted chocolate, cocoa and flavoring; blend thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream; pour into chilled crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Cool at room temperature, then chill at least 5 hours before serving. Freezes well.

title: fudge pecan pie
directions: Melt butter with cocoa in saucepan.
Add hot water and mix well.
Add sugar, flour, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix until smooth.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Place on preheated baking sheet and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until set.
Top with whipped topping.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: korean short ribs
directions: Marinate meat for approximately 1 hour or more.
Marinade is good for pork, chicken or beef.
Meat can be broiled, barbecued or baked at 350° for 1 hour.

title: jello-cream cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Chill and let set slightly. Whip Dream Whip and set aside.
Cream the cream cheese and add to jello.
Add crushed pineapple. Fold in Dream Whip with electric mixer. Add celery and nuts. Mold and chill.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and shape into a ball.
Roll in crushed nuts (optional).

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix and beat 8 minutes.
Grease Bundt pan and sprinkle 1/4 cup chopped pecans in pan.
Layer with cake mixture and filling.

title: snowberry cookies
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Stir in last three ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: spanakopita
directions: Drain cottage cheese and spinach.
Mix and chop.
Add Feta cheese, oregano and nutmeg.
Heat olive oil and saute onion. Scrape into cheese mixture.
Add pepper and olives.
Butter baking sheet and cut phyllo dough in half lengthwise and in half lengthwise again.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush top piece of phyllo with butter.
Take off pile and lay on counter in front of you. Butter 2nd sheet and lay on first.
Re-cover pile with plastic. Put filling in corner and fold as a flag.
Make triangles.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve.

title: golfer's delight
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients well with hands (crust).
Press down firmly in dish.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes until light brown at 350°.
Cream together with mixer the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Spread over pecan crust.
Beat with fork until thick the pudding with milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, then pour over cream cheese mixture.
Spread remainder of Cool Whip on top.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Mix together bread, onion and eggs with enough chicken broth or water and butter to make a thin custard.
Cook in double boiler until thick.
Beat while cooking.
While it is still a little warm, add ground chicken.
Chill.
Mold into croquettes (1/3 cup each). Dip in beaten egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry in hot lard or Crisco.

title: mom's breakfast casserole
directions: Crumble and brown sausage and drain well.
Layer hash browns, sausage and cheese in bottom of baking dish.
Beat eggs, milk, dry ingredients and optional ingredients together and pour over layers.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until eggs are done.
Can be prepared the night before for morning baking.

title: brownie cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine Crisco, sugar, water and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed, then beat in eggs. Combine dry ingredients until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Drop by tablespoons 2 inches apart.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes. Do not overbake.

title: holiday egg nog
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs until light and foamy.
Add sugar and salt, beating until thick.
Chill at least 3 hours.
Add nutmeg to suit your taste.
Yield:
12 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix together.
Use as spread with assorted crackers.

title: royal fruit salad
directions: Combine lemon gelatin with unflavored gelatin and pour boiling water over the combine gelatins, stirring until the gelatin is dissolved.
Open can of fruit cocktail and pour the juice off the fruit and into the gelatin.
Mix mayonnaise into the fruit in the can.
Stir until the mayonnaise is no longer lumpy, then add to gelatin, stirring well.
After cooling, pour into a container to mold and congeal in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin spice delight
directions: Blend first 5 ingredients with pumpkin pie spice.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle
cake
mix
over
top. Dribble melted oleo over top.
Sprinkle
with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Better if baked day before and refrigerated.
Cut into squares and serve with Cool Whip.

title: southwest chili pot
directions: Melt butter in 6-quart Dutch oven.
Add onion and garlic and cook until tender, but not brown (about 8 minutes).
Add ground beef, chili powder, cumin seed, bay leaves, salt, paprika and Tabasco.
Break up meat with large cooking spoon as it cooks.
Cook until meat is brown throughout.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste and stir well.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Stir in beans and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Makes 5 quarts (12 servings).

title: mexican cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread and cool.
Crumble, then combine all ingredients.
Chill 1 hour before serving.

title: hard rock candy
directions: Mix the sugar, corn syrup and water in medium saucepan. Insert candy thermometer. Bring to 300° or hard crack stage. Remove pan from heat. Quickly add the flavoring and food coloring; mix.
Pour onto well-greased cookie sheet.
Allow to cool and crack into bite size pieces.
If desired, you can sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix together, shape into balls and freeze.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes or until browned.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine milk, honey and salt.
Combine flour and shortening in a separate bowl, cutting shortening in.
Slowly add the liquid and dry ingredients together and mix well.
Roll out as if for pie crust except cut into lattice strips (1/2 to 1-inch wide).
Place strips in a crisscross pattern (or checkerboard) in the bottom of baking pan and place another layer on top after filling is added.

title: chili verde
directions: Cut roast into cubes, trimming fat.
Place in a large pan or Dutch oven on medium heat.
Cut onion and garlic.
Place in pan with meat browning.
Put bouillon cubes into 2 cups of very hot water and let dissolve.
Cut chilies into strips.
Pour water into pan.
Put in chilies and seasonings.
Put on medium heat and let simmer until meat is very tender, 4 hours.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, sugar, salt, flour, eggs and raisins over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture coats the spoon.
Add rice, vanilla, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Cool and serve with whipped topping, or may be served hot.

title: eight minute light-n-fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water, stirring about 3 minutes.
Add ice cubes and stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove any unmelted ice.

title: rainbow cake
directions: Place cake layers, top side up, in 2 clean layer pans; prick each cake with a utility fork at 1/2-inch intervals.
Dissolve each flavor gelatin separately in one cup of boiling water and carefully spoon each over one of the cake layers.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Dip one cake pan in warm water for 10 seconds; turn out onto a serving plate.
Top with one cup of whipped topping.
Unmold second cake layer; place carefully on first layer.
Frost top and sides with remaining whipped topping.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and salt.
Add water and stir together.
In large bowl mix flour, sugar and butter.
Sprinkle over apple mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian pie
directions: Mix crumbs, margarine and sugar.
Press into a large casserole dish.
Slice bananas and place on crumb crust.
Mix milk and ReaLemon.
Pour over bananas.
Add drained crushed pineapple.
Add a layer of Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Top with cherries.

title: swiss treats
directions: Cream shortening, sugar.
In seperate bowl, beat egg, add vanilla.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add to mixture, stir well.
Batter will be thick, don't worry.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Grease 16x11-inch pan.
Spread dough in pan evenly.
Bake at 375° for 20 min.
Let cool a while, then cut into squares.

title: banana creme parfait
directions: Mix yogurt and pudding.
Add bananas and mix.
Top with Cool Whip.
Crush graham cracker and sprinkle over top.
Very low calorie!!

title: lon piergues chop suey
directions: Fry meat.
Add onions.
When brown, add celery, 2 cups water, molasses and sauce.
Cook until meat is tender.
Thicken with 1 tablespoon cornstarch.
Mushrooms may be added.
Serves 2 generously.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all together, except Rice Krispies.
Place in baking dish and put browned Rice Krispies on top.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook first four ingredients to hard boil, stirring occasionally.
Add butter, vanilla, nuts and then beat.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: You will also need vegetable cooking spray.

title: pressure cooker pot roast
directions: Brown meat in cooker (uncovered) with small amount of hot oil. When completely brown on both sides, add a little salt and pepper. Add onion slices and water (1 cup for 4-quart cooker or 1 1/4 cups for 6 to 8-quart cooler).
Set pressure control for 10 pounds (both sizes).
After control starts to jiggle, cook for 60 minutes. Adjust heat for control to jiggle 1 to 3 times a minute.
Cool cooker 5 minutes then place under cold running water to reduce pressure.
Remove meat.
Remove onion if not desired to be in gravy.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Slice apples; use as dip.

title: beef marinade
directions: Mix ingredients.
Marinate meat overnight in refrigerator. Bake in marinade, turning once.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onions, celery and broccoli for 5 to 8 minutes.
Stir in cheese, soup and canned milk until smooth.
Put cooked rice in greased 8-inch square baking dish. Pour cheese mixture over.
Do not stir.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: bean and pasta soup
directions: Bring water to a boil in a large saucepan. Stir in pasta, celery, lima beans, soup mix and basil.
Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in pork and beans and tomatoes.
Cook until thoroughly heated.

title: boiled pineapple
directions: Pat rings dry.
Put in low buttered pan.
Drizzle with butter and honey.
Broil about 4-inches from heat for 2 to 3 minutes until bubbly.
Serve on warm plates with 2 tablespoons of yogurt.

title: oven stroganoff(smells so good!)
directions: Cut meat into bite-sized pieces.
Do not brown.
Just mix all ingredients, except the sour cream, in a large casserole or roast pan (for double quantity).
Bake at 300°, uncovered, for three hours.
Just before serving, stir in sour cream.
Serve over buttered wide noodles.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Put all ingredients in soup pot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil.
Simmer 1/2 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: seduction cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat chocolate chips and pecans in a spoonful or two of dry cake mix.
Mix remaining ingredients together and fold in chocolate chips and pecans. Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or tube pan and bake for 50 minutes.

title: chocolate chip date cake
directions: Cover dates with baking soda and hot water.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs, vanilla and salt together.
Add flour and liquid from dates, a little at a time, until mixed well.
Add dates and mix. Place cake batter in well buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sourdough waffles
directions: Separate egg whites and yolks; beat whites until stiff, but not dry.
Combine egg yolks, oil and salt; beat until smooth. Stir in Sourdough Starter (see recipe in this section).

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use blender to chop cranberries.
Do not peel apples; cut small or chop with blender.
Mix together cranberries, apples, pineapple and sugar.
Mix jello with hot water and add to fruit.
Add nuts. Place in refrigerator until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: uncle gordon's chicken fingers
directions: Cut chicken fillets into strips.
Salt and pepper meat to taste. Mix eggs and milk in a small bowl.
Roll chicken strips in flour, then dip in egg and milk mixture.
Roll strips in flour again.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: In heavy saucepan, bring 2 cups of milk, uncooked rice and raisins to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and cook over very low heat about 15 minutes or until rice is tender.
Remove from heat; stir in butter until melted.
In mixing bowl, stir together the eggs, 2 cups of milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir rice mixture into egg mixture.
Pour into a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish (9 x 13-inch also works well).
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes. Stir well.
Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes more until a knife inserted at the center comes out clean. Serve warm or chilled.

title: orange treat cake
directions: Prepare cake mix substituting 1 1/2 cups whipped topping for oil or butter.
Bake in two greased and floured 9-inch layer pans about 30 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Heat milk and marshmallows until marshmallows are melted.
Let cool.
Add strawberries and whipped cream.
Line the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Add strawberry mixture. Top with more vanilla wafer crumbs.
Refrigerate until set up.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: In a large bowl, cream butter and sugar using electric mixer. Add vanilla, scraping down bowl as needed.
Add flour and salt, mixing until thoroughly combined.
Roll tablespoons of dough into small balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place dough balls on lightly greased cookie sheet about 1-inch apart.
Press down the center of each ball with a spoon, forming a depression.
Fill each with a teaspoonful of preserves or nuts.
Bake in 325° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Transfer cookies immediately to a cool, flat surface.
When cookies are completely cool, dust with confectioners sugar.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: chocolate peanut butter pie
directions: In the top of a double boiler, over hot but not boiling water, combine sugar, flour and salt. Gradually add milk and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour a small amount of the hot milk mixture into the egg yolks; return all to double boiler. Cook for 4 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from the heat; stir in vanilla. Cool for about 10 minutes.

title: chicken rotel
directions: Saute onion and pepper in 1 stick oleo; add broth and tomatoes. Cook for 10 minutes.
Stir and break up tomatoes.
Add diced cheese, peas and chicken.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Cook noodles in chicken broth.
Mix noodles and sauce.
Place in large baking dish; bake in 350° oven until bubbly.

title: russian dump chicken
directions: Mix onion soup mix, add 8-16 oz. of Russian dressing and apricot jam together, mix well, about 3 minutes, pour over chicken. Place chicken in a crockpot or slow cooker.
Pour mixture over chicken and cook for 6-8 hours on low or 4-5 hours on high.
Serve over a bed of steamed or cooked rice.

title: yeasty pancakes
directions: Dissolve yeast well in warm water. Pour milk and egg into a blender. Put on top and blend on low speed for about one minute. Add the yeast/water mixture and Bisquick mix. Blend well for about 2 or 3 minutes on low speed. Set in refrigerator overnight. Pour onto hot, greased griddle and turn when bubbles form on top. Good with maple syrup or warm sweetened strawberries and Cool whip.

title: blt dip
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients. Chill if desired. Makes 3 cups.

title: kosher dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Chill in ice water and pack in jars.
To jar, add all ingredients, except vinegar, salt and water.
Combine salt, water and vinegar; boil.
Pour into jars and seal.
(Heat jars in pan of hot water to seal.)

title: unstuffed cabbage
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain; reserve.
Saute onion until tender.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add bacon, rice, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
In small kettle, put crushed tomatoes, brown sugar, vinegar, thyme and remaining salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Arrange 1/3 of cabbage in a 3-quart dish; spoon 1/2 meat mixture over, then half of sauce.
Repeat, layering, ending with cabbage and sauce.
Poke bay leaf into center.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 hour, or until cabbage is tender.
Remove bay leaf.

title: crepes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and be sure it is smooth.
Fry in a small skillet in a small amount of butter.
Cook vegetables (carrots and broccoli).
Salt and season.
Then roll vegetables in crepes and put in a baking dish.
Saute onions in butter.
Make a white sauce of flour and milk.
Cook white sauce in onions; add at least 8 ounces of shredded cheese.
Pour over crepes and heat to serve.

title: classic hamburger casserole
directions: In medium skillet, brown ground beef; drain.
Stir in green beans, soup, water, seasonings and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
In medium bowl, combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can onions.
Spoon potato mixture in mounds around edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes, or until heated through.
Top potatoes with cheese and remaining can of onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes, or until onions are golden brown.

title: blueberry tumble
directions: Combine berries, sugar and cinnamon.
Cook over low heat 15 minutes.
Cool slightly and spoon into dessert dishes.
In small bowl combine granola, coconut and butter and spoon over berries. Serve.

title: ham barbecue
directions: Mix all together.
Cook to a boil and add ham.
Let sit for flavors to blend.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate chips in a double boiler.
Separate eggs.
Beat yolks and add to melted chocolate chips (not too hot).
Beat the whites stiff.
Fold into chocolate chips and egg yolks.
Pour in a 9-inch baked pie shell.
Refrigerate and when cool top with whipped cream.

title: french fried mushrooms
directions: Mix and set aside for 1 hour. Dip mushrooms 10 minutes before you fry. Fry at 375°.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Mix bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, salt and parsley.
Add garlic, mustard and Worcestershire sauce to the melted butter. Dip chicken in the butter mixture, then in bread crumbs.
Place in a large shallow pan and drizzle with remaining butter.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: turtle stew 2
directions: Prepare a roux by heating oil and bacon drippings in a skillet.
Add flour gradually while stirring and cook until deeply browned.
Add onions and pepper.
Cook until tender and then add parsley and garlic.
Cook a few minutes and add 4 cups cold water. Stir until the mixture is smooth.
Add wine, lemon juice and Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with cayenne.
While roux is cooking, salt and pepper the turtle meat and brown in cooking oil. Add this to the roux and cook for about 2 hours.
Add water if the stew becomes too thick.
Serve over rice or pasta.

title: one dish roast beef with veggies
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Put meat on foil (enough to wrap up meat and veggies, 2 to 2 1/2 feet).
Stir together mushroom and onion soups; spread on meat.
Put veggies on top and around.
Sprinkle water on veggies (use less if using mushrooms).
(I also sometimes season meat with garlic salt and pepper.)
Fold foil over and seal securely.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: bacon, lettuce and tomato salad
directions: Saute bacon until crisp. Drain on paper towels. Crumble and set aside. In a large straight-sided glass salad bowl, arrange salad in layers this way: crumbled bacon; Romaine, broken into bite-sized pieces; cherry tomato halves; broccoli, cut into small flowerettes; red onion, thinly sliced.

title: deluxe potato soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and celery in margarine.
Add potatoes, water, bouillon, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: nestle's quik brownies
directions: Blend
sugar and Wesson oil.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour
into
greased	and floured 10 x 15-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Heat soup.
Do not boil.
Mix gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water. Stir into soup and cool.
Crush 1 can shrimp with fork (may use blender, but only for a second; if over blended can make mixture too thin).
Mix with other ingredients.
Layer mixture with second can of whole shrimp*.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: tamale pie
directions: In heavy, large skillet, saute onion, green pepper and garlic. Add finely broken up ground beef.
Brown meat until it no longer looks reddish.
Mix in beans, corn, soup and water.
Season with salt, pepper and chili powder.
Simmer about 15 minutes.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix 1 package cornbread mix according to package.
Spread over meat mixture.
Place in oven and bake at 425° until cornbread is done.
Eat hot.

title: taco bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown ground meat and onion; drain.
Spoon into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish or size you wish.
Stir seasoning mix, tomato sauce and corn; stir remaining ingredients until blended and pour over beef mixture.
Sprinkle with the cheese. Bake until golden brown.
Serve with sour cream and chopped tomatoes, if desired.

title: banana bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease loaf pan with shortening.
Mix sugar, bananas, oil and eggs in bowl with a wooden spoon.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Let cool 10 minutes. Remove from pan.
Let cool completely before slicing.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine stuffing crumbs and butter; set aside.
Place chicken in shallow, ungreased baking dish.
Top with cheese, soup, water and crumbs.
Bake for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°, uncovered.

title: minty grasshopper pie
directions: With mixer, beat cream cheese until fluffy; gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Stir in food coloring. Add crushed cookies, fold in cool whip, and pour into pie crust. Chill at least 3 hours. Garnish as desired. Serve chilled. Refrigerate leftovers. Servings 8. May top with chocolate shavings, additional cookie pieces or mint leaves.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Measure 1/4 cup water and 1/2 cup syrup in measuring cup (put water in cup first). Pour 1 1/2 cups sugar along with water and syrup in a large iron skillet and mix well. Bring to a boil on high and then reduce heat to medium-high and add the peanuts and pinch of salt. Bring back to a boil and cook on medium-high heat (keep it stirred or it will burn) until syrup turns a reddish brown or peanuts pop (about 10 to 12 minutes). Add the vanilla and butter and stir well, then add the soda (this is the last item to add), stirring quickly, then pour into a large shallow 4-sided buttered cookie sheet. Spread mixture over evenly in pan and make sure air bubbles are out. Ensure that you have the cookie sheet ready when mixture is ready to pour or it will overcook. After it has cooled for about 30 minutes or when you can twist the sheet and it pops out, it is ready to break into pieces and put in a covered jar.

title: pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients ahead of serving (except bacon/ham and nuts).
Toss well.
Add bacon and nuts over top.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: summer squash
directions: Wash squash; slice.
Bring water to a boil and boil squash and onion together until tender.
Place squash and onion in layers with cracker crumbs, butter, salt and pepper.
Top with cheese and bake until cheese is brown.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and put into greased casserole dish.

title: chocolate eclair
directions: Mix pudding as directed and add Cool Whip.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with crackers and alternate with pudding.
Spread frosting over last layer of crackers.
Put in refrigerator.

title: skillet meal
directions: Shape beef into patties and brown in fat.
Remove meat and saute onions, mushrooms and peppers in pan, reserving 4 thick slices of onions and 4 rings of green peppers.
Return patties to skillet, laying onion slices and green pepper slices on top of each patty.
Add noodles and tomatoes and simmer with lid for 45 minutes.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar, then beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add milk and eggs to mixture.
Fold in bananas, vanilla and nuts.
Bake in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: english trifle
directions: Line a glass bowl with ladyfingers, sides and bottoms; then sprinkle with a package of dry cherry jello.
Dribble sherry over this, then slice bananas over all.
Spread with Cool Whip.
Chill. This dessert is better made the day before serving.
This can be made in a fancy bowl and served from the table.

title: sue's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix first four ingredients and bring to a boil.
Boil for 4 minutes.
Turn off heat and mix in peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme.
Stir until mixture begins to thicken.
Pour into buttered dish and let set.

title: e-z peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in baking dish (deep and or dish). Mix flour, sugar, milk and cinnamon. Mix well. Pour batter over melted butter. Do not stir! Top with peaches and juice. Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Can serve with whipped cream.

title: baked mashed potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour if warm.
If refrigerated, bake at 350° for 1 hour.
This is a good mashed potato dish to make ahead of time, then all you have to do is put it in the oven an hour before serving.
Sometimes, I add a little half and half to get a smoother consistency.

title: wonderful ham, vegetable and barley soup
directions: Cook ham bone in 6 cups water with sliced onions, garlic and bay leaf.
Simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bone and add ham scraps, tomatoes, peppers, potato, carrots, celery and barley.
Simmer for an hour.

title: sneaky spaghetti sauce
directions: Grate up zucchini and carrot and saute in a little olive oil with garlic, oregano, basil, salt and pepper to taste.
Add puree, paste and a little water to desired consistency and let simmer for up to 5 hours (the longer the better!).
Or use your favorite spaghetti sauce recipe, adding the zucchini and carrot for added body and nutrients.
The kids (and dad) don't have to know they're eating their vegetables.

title: impossible quiche
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in blender.
Lightly grease deep pan with Crisco; pour in mixture.
Press down the Swiss cheese and diced ham, bacon or crab.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: holiday hot nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in a 9-inch baking dish (1/4-inch thickness).
Sprinkle diced vegetables over cream cheese.
Top with 1/2 bag Monterey Jack cheese.
Pour whole bottle of chili sauce over vegetables and cheese.
Sprinkle remaining Monterey Jack over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until cheese is melted.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Saute crawfish and onion in butter until onions are soft (about 10 minutes).
Set aside.
Combine corn meal, salt, baking soda, baking powder, garlic powder, milk, eggs and corn.
Mix well.
Grease a large baking pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Layer 1/2 corn meal mixture on bottom.
Next pour crawfish-onion mixture over. Then evenly spread a layer of cheese.
Sprinkle with peppers.
Top with remaining corn meal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: delicious squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine and stir in stuffing.
Line casserole with 1/2 of the stuffing mix.
Combine all other ingredients and spoon into casserole.
Cover with remainder of stuffing.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: salad dressing chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given. Bake in a 9 x 13 pan 25 minutes at 350°. It's good with a powdered sugar frosting with butter in it.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook burger and onion in frying pan until done; drain.
Then put in a 9 x 12-inch pan (spread out).
Put both soups over the top and spread over burger, then place cheese on top of this. Last, place Tater Tots on top.
Cook until Tater Tots are done.

title: bubble recipe
directions: Combine.
Stir well.
Let set several hours before using.
Can be stored in fridge to extend its life, but let warm to use.

title: country fried corn
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Add corn, sugar and butter to drippings in skillet.
Salt and pepper. Crumble bacon back into skillet.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes on medium heat.

title: creme de menthe
directions: Mix sugar and water.
Boil 8 minutes.
Cool, add extract, coloring and vodka.
Bottle and shake well.
Ready for use.

title: thai beef salad
directions: Grill the beef over charcoal.
Slice it into strips 1/8-inch thick.
Put in a large bowl.
Peel the onion, slice it and add to beef.
Add the lime juice and fish sauce.
Mix well.
(You can add cucumber and tomatoes.)
Arrange a single layer of lettuce leaves on a serving platter and place the beef mixture on top.
Garnish with sprigs of coriander and mint.

title: carrot cake icing
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter; add sugar and vanilla. Spread on layers and sprinkle with nuts.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Prepare chocolate cake batter as directed.
Spoon into 18 greased muffin cups.
Bake 20 minutes, cool completely on wire racks.
Using 1 tub Cool Whip (thawed), spread on bottoms and sides of cupcakes.
Roll in coconut.
Place cupcakes top sides down on serving plate.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake 20 to 25 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool, then frost.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti; set aside. In same pot, combine soup, water and cheese. Heat until cheese melts. Add rest of ingredients and then add spaghetti. Heat through and serve. YUMMY!!!

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix by hand, do not use mixer.
In a bowl combine sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt, cinnamon and soda.
Add to first mixture, with oil.
Add fruit and nuts.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Let cool in pan 20 to 25 minutes.
Glaze with frosting.

title: raised doughnuts
directions: Combine and fry in deep fat.

title: cheesy squash casserole
directions: Wash and slice squash in large pan.
Cover with water.
Add butter.
Cook until tender.
Drain, mash squash.
Add cracker crumbs and onions.
Stir well.
Add 3/4 of cheese.
Add eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour into buttered casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until cheese and cracker crumbs are brown.

title: yankee noodle
directions: Brown meat and onion in small amount of fat.
Add tomatoes. Season and bring to a boil.
Add noodles; cover tightly.
Cook 20 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Stir jello into the boiled water until dissolved. Add strawberries, bananas, pineapple and pecans. Pour 1/2 of mixture (I use a 12 x 9 Pyrex dish) into dish. Set into refrigerator for an hour or until firm. Set the other half on the table so as not to set. Spread Cool Whip completely over the set dish. Add the rest of the mixture over the Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: marvelous eggs
directions: In 2-quart glass casserole, heat butter 30 seconds.
Add onion and cook for 2 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in eggs, milk, salt and lemon juice.
Cook, covered, 4 to 5 minutes, stirring every 2 minutes.
When almost set, lightly fold in cream cheese.
Cook one minute longer, rest 5 minutes, serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Boil first 6 ingredients together until thick.
Add vanilla. Pour into pie crust that has been baked.
Make meringue of the two egg whites.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and stir in rice, chicken, soup, milk, half of cheese and onion.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all together.
Place in loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Turn out onto plate.

title: lubi and rice
directions: Saute onions then garlic in pot.
Brown meat.
Add tomato paste diluted with water.
Add string beans, salt, pepper and allspice.
Simmer as long as you want.

title: quick blueberry dump cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan. Dump in the pie filling, nuts, pineapple and cake mix; stir lightly to blend. Top with dots of butter and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pudding-pecan pie
directions: Combine
pie filling with corn syrup. With mixer, blend at low speed.
Add
milk	and egg.
Blend well. Stir in nuts. Pour into pie
shell. Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool at least 3 hours before serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: In large frypan saute onion in oil until soft.
In bowl combine ketchup, sugar, soy sauce, lemon juice and pepper.
Add to pan with onions.
Add chicken.
Bring to boil.
Cover and simmer 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is done.
Remove chicken.
Dissolve cornstarch with 2 tablespoons water.
Add to pan.
Bring sauce to boil, stirring until thickened.
Pour over chicken.
Serve with rice.

title: marinade for flank steak
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Pour over scored flank steaks day or two before serving.
Turn occasionally.
Cook over hot charcoal. Slice into thin diagonal strips.
Marinade may be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: lentil-barley stew
directions: Saute in large iron pot margarine, celery and onion until tender.
Add water and lentils, cook 20 minutes, uncovered.
Then add tomatoes, barley and spices.
Simmer 45 to 60 minutes, covered.

title: mother-in-law cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, baking soda, salt and sugar.
Make a well in the center.
Drain pineapple, saving 1/3 cup of juice.
Add syrup, crushed pineapple, molasses, eggs and soft butter to flour mixture.
Beat with large spoon until mixed.
Pour batter into prepared pan; spread with spatula.
Sprinkle with nuts and brown sugar.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Remove to rack.
Cut into 12 squares.
Serve with whipped cream.
Tastes better if made day before.

title: autumn soup
directions: *One 28 ounce can of tomatoes with liquid can be substituted; reduce water to 3 cups.

title: carrot-wheat muffins
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a medium bowl; set aside. Combine egg and remaining ingredients in a small bowl.
Stir well and let stand 3 minutes.
Make a well in center of flour mixture. Add cereal mixture to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon mixture into greased muffin pans, filling three-fourths full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: spicy cocktail sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups water, tomato paste, horseradish, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce, ground red pepper and salt. Simmer 10 minutes until thickens.
Cover and chill several hours. Makes 2 cups.

title: wonderful shrimp dip
directions: Mix together and serve chilled with Fritos.

title: cheese ball
directions: Toast chopped pecans in margarine; set aside.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Roll into a ball.
Roll ball in toasted nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Thaw and drain California Blend.
Combine soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimiento and half can of onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with rest of cheese and onions. Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes more.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy (in-a-hurry) goulash
directions: Make macaroni and cheese as directed on box.
Brown hamburg (drain off fat); add stewed tomatoes.
Mix in macaroni and cheese mixture; simmer just long enough to blend flavors.

title: cabbage soup
directions: In large pot, cook cabbage in water until tender.
Add tomatoes, onion, salt and pepper to taste (the more pepper, the better the soup is), mushrooms and sausage or hot dogs.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cook until meat is brown.
Add onion, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add tomato soup.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add sharp cheese.
Cook slowly until cheese is melted.
Add rice. Cool.
Cut peppers lengthwise, remove seeds.
Boil in water for 3 minutes.
Remove and drain.
Cool slightly.
Stuff with filling and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 small loaf pans.
Pour equal amounts in each and bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broiled salmon with lemon and olive oil
directions: Stir together first 6 ingredients in a shallow dish or large ziptop plastic bag; add pork chops.
Cover or seal and chill 30 minutes, turning once.
Remove pork from marinade, reserving marinade.

Grill pork, covered with grill lid, over medium-high heat (350° to 400°) about 10 to 12 minutes or until a meat thermometer inserted into thickest portion registers 160°, turning once. Bring reserved marinade to a boil in a small saucepan and cook, stirring occasionally, 2 minutes.
Pour over chops before serving.

title: taco dip
directions: Spread 2 cans bean dip (any or your favorite brand) in shallow bake pan for first layer.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Cut up the artichoke hearts.
Add the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake in a pie plate at 350° for 20 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: corned beef dip
directions: Mix all the ingredients in a bowl.
Cover and chill for a few hours.
Hollow out a round loaf of Italian bread.
Cut center into wedges.
Put hollow bread on a serving dish.
Fill the center with the dip.
Place bread wedges on platter to use for dip.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix onion and lime juice. Let stand for 20 minutes, then add all other ingredients. Chill and serve.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Use a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Layer the pineapple, then the fruit filling.
Next, sprinkle the entire box of dry cake mix.
Cover top with pats of oleo.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
After baking 40 minutes, take out of oven and sprinkle with pecans and return to oven and bake about 10 to 15 minutes more.

title: stephanie's grilled tuna melts
directions: Mix the tuna and mayonnaise together; set aside.
Mix butter, garlic and Parmesan into a thick paste.
Butter the bread with the mixture.
Place 4 slices of bread on a grill.
Layer with tuna mixture and 1 slice cheese for each bread.
Top each with second piece of bread.
Grill until golden brown.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients:
lettuce first, then in order: peas, onion rings, mayonnaise, sugar, Parmesan cheese and bacon.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate before serving.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In a large bowl, put a layer of 1/2 the brownies broken up and then add 1/2 the pudding, 1/2 Heath bars and 1/2 Cool Whip. Repeat layers and then refrigerate.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Melt about 1/2 cup oleo in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle the pecans and coconut in pan.
Mix the cake mix according to directions and pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix together the cream cheese, 1 cup oleo and the powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Best eaten while still warm.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put cabbage, meat, peppers, onion, salt and pepper in pot. Cover.
Cook over medium heat for 1 1/2 hours or until cabbage is tender.
Stir in rice; mix well.
Pour in large casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes at 300°.

title: san francisco joe
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole.
Place in 400° oven and bake until warm throughout.
Cut into squares and serve with fruit salad and croissants.

title: lemon jello cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: bubble bread
directions: Mix sugar, melted butter and cinnamon together in a bowl.
Cut bread in halves lengthwise, then into small pieces.
Roll pieces into sugar mixture.
Place into greased Bundt pan and let rise to top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Let cool and pull apart.

title: tahini nut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Shape into balls.
Place on an oiled cookie sheet.
Flatten slightly.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Let cool and harden before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: raisin pasty
directions: Cook raisins for a few minutes on low light until soft, but not mushy.
Line cookie sheet with pastry.
Spread mixture on, then sprinkle with mint.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Cut into squares.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine graham cracker crumbs and 1 stick of margarine, melted, and spread
over bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; chill.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and 2 sticks margarine until fluffy.
Spread over cracker crumb mixture. Place cut up bananas over powdered sugar mixture.
Sprinkle pineapple around and between bananas. Spread Cool Whip over top and garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg.
Add flour, baking powder, milk and vanilla.
Stir in blueberries.
Pour into greased muffin pans or cupcake paper. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: sausage-egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Place in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover with cheese.
Break eggs gently over cheese, placing them individually throughout dish.
Pour half and half easily around eggs just leaving the egg yolks showing.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until set.
Great for company!

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Layer the bean dip, avocado dip, sour cream mix, tomatoes or salsa, black olives and shredded Cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy italian salad
directions: Store a garlic clove in a small jar of oil and keep refrigerated.
Pour this oil over lettuce, then add red wine vinegar and Parmesan cheese and toss.
Add more or less according to taste.
No more bottled dressings! Enjoy!

title: rice stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine rice, 2 cups water and salt. Bring to a boil. Simmer 40 minutes or until rice is tender. Add parsley and almonds; mix and set aside. Bring 1 cup water to boil. Add onion soup mix. Set aside. Cut deep pockets in chops; brown in hot oil. Cool. Stuff with rice mixture and place in a 2-quart casserole. Pour onion soup mixture over chops. Sprinkle with pepper. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender. Yield: 2 servings.

title: gazpacho
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve cold.
It's delicious!

title: tomato gravy
directions: Save tomato cans and fill with water.
In a Dutch oven, place oil and heat.
Put vegetables in and saute until clear.
Add flour to pot and fry until brown.
In a blender or food processor, put in tomato products.
When blended, put in pot and cook for about 15 minutes.
Put water from cans in pot, plus add about 1 cup more (until right consistency, not too thick or thin).
Salt and pepper to taste.
Let cook for 1 hour.

title: pumpkin applesauce bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly grease two 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl, beat shortening and sugar with an electric mixer on high until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Fold in applesauce and pumpkin.
Mix flour, baking soda, salt, baking powder and spices.
Stir into pumpkin mixture in thirds, alternating with apple juice.
Divide batter evenly between the two pans.
Bake about 1 hour, until tester inserted in the centers comes out clean.

title: sweet and spicy meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients. Roll out walnut sized meatballs (about 100). Bake on a cookie sheet for 25 minutes at 350°. Transfer to baking or serving dish and cover with sauce.

title: cornbread
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients, then add rest of mix.
Beat just until well blended.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mandarin orange salad
directions: Mix and chill overnight.

title: chicken livers in madeira sauce
directions: Cover chicken livers with milk.
Soak 2 hours.
Drain; discard milk.
Saute onion in fat/butter.
Mix flour and salt.
Coat livers with seasoned flour.
Add liver to onions.
Stir-fry just to golden (about 5 minutes).
Stir in broth and wine.
Cover. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes or just until livers are tender.

title: aunt jewel's bean soup
directions: Wash
beans
and cook slowly in water 2 1/2 to 3 hours. Cook onions, celery and pepper in margarine until tender.
Add to beans
with
tomatoes
and	other seasonings and simmer at least 30 minutes.
Can be frozen.
May use Ro-Tel tomatoes and green chilies.

title: no bake butterscotch cake
directions: Mix flour, sugars and butter in a bowl. Remove 1/2 cup of mixture and set aside. Add vanilla and milk. Stir in remaining ingredients. Mix well. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Place butterscotch chips on top and sprinkle over cake the rest of butter mixture you set aside. Bake 40 minutes at 350°. Cool in pan.

title: seven layer salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook peas as package label directs, but only for 1 minute.
Drain.
In large glass salad bowl, layer lettuce, celery, green pepper and peas.
Spread mayo evenly on top.
Sprinkle on the cheese, then bacon.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Do not toss at serving time.
Makes 12 servings with 350 calories.

title: buffet mushroom hors d'oeuvres
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms.
Brush mushroom cups with butter. Brush cookie sheet lightly with butter.
Arrange mushrooms on cookie sheet.
Chop stems.
Brown bacon and drain on absorbent towels.
Crumble bacon.

title: debbie's corn pudding
directions: Mix all together; top with margarine and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: brownie cheese cherry
directions: Bake brownies as directed on box.
Cool.
Top with Jell-O cheese cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
Top with cherry pie filling when ready.

title: "paella valenciana"(a traditional spanish dish for holiday festivities)
directions: Wash chicken pieces and pat dry.
In large skillet, brown chicken in oil.
Remove chicken.
Pour off fat.
Add onion and tomatoes; cook and stir 5 minutes or until onion is tender.
Stir in rice, broth and next seasonings.
Add chicken.

title: orange butter cake
directions: Combine first 12 ingredients in large mixing bowl; beat at low speed with an electric mixer until blended.
Beat at high speed 3 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans on wire racks 10 minutes; remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.

title: pecan pie muffins
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in the center of mixture.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Stir together eggs and butter; add to dry ingredients.
Place foil baking cup (remove paper liners) in muffin pans and coat with cooking spray.
Spoon batter into cups, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans immediately and cool on wire rack.

title: monterey pizza rice
directions: Combine all ingredients, except green pepper and cheese in 10-inch skillet.
Bring to boil, reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Stir in green pepper.
Remove from heat.
Let stand, covered, until all liquid is absorbed (5 minutes).
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 5 servings.

title: doreen's custard pudding
directions: Blend hot water and Hi-Energy Vanilla Supplement.
Add egg, cottage cheese and sweetener.
Pour in bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg.
Place in a large bowl of hot water and microwave for about 3 minutes.

title: ranch cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese soften. Put into bowl. Chop beef and onion. Stir well. Add Ranch. Stir again. Chill for 1 1/2 hours. Serve with crackers and sliced cucumbers.

title: "biscottas" - queen's biscuits
directions: Cream sugar, butter and Crisco until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients to creamed mixture; add milk last and mix well.
Roll into 2 1/2-inch finger shape length.
Roll in sesame seed and bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: reese cup balls
directions: Pour butter into large bowl; add peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Work by hand and form small balls.
Set aside on wax paper.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and celery.
Drain.
Then add catsup, chili sauce, mustard, sugar, salt, pepper and water.
Simmer about 10 minutes and serve on rolls.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Chop the broccoli, onion and tomato.
Mix all ingredients together.
Allow to chill 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: crab quiche
directions: Beat eggs with wire whip.
Add all ingredients, except flour; blend slightly.
Take wire whip and blend in flour.
Cook in electric skillet at 260° to 300° until done, 35 to 40 minutes. Garnish with sliced tomatoes, avocado slices and a dollop of sour cream.

title: microwave pineapple muffin
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl, cream together pineapple, brown sugar and butter.
Beat in egg and reserved syrup.
Add flour, nuts, baking powder and salt, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Turn batter into 8 (6 ounce) custard cups lined with cupcake papers.
Arrange 4 custard cups on a round baking tray.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 2 1/2 to 4 minutes. Repeat procedure with remaining 4 custard cups.
Let muffins stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 muffins.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Grease pie pan.
Mix Bisquick, pudding, margarine, egg, milk, vanilla and 2 teaspoons of sugar together. Pour into pie pan.

title: sugar-free diabetic bars
directions: Boil water, raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and oil 3 minutes.
Set aside to cool.
Mix warm water, soda, sweetener, salt and baking powder.
Set aside.
Beat 1 egg well.
Add second mixture.
Mix well.
Add applesauce and first mixture; beat well.
Blend in flour.
If needed, use more applesauce to make batter.
Add nuts. Bake at 350° about 30 minutes in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: crunchy chocolate sauce
directions: In a skillet saute nuts in butter until golden.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips till melted.
Serve warm over ice cream.
As sauce cools it forms a hard shell.
Store in refrigerator.
Sauce can be reheated in the microwave.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: tuna-rice patties
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients and stir well. In a large, heavy skillet over medium heat, heat enough oil to cover bottom.
Drop tuna mixture by tablespoons and flatten slightly.
Fry 6 to 7 minutes on each side or until golden and firm.
Leftovers make good sandwiches.

title: happle bagel sandwich(great for kids!)
directions: Slice apple into round pieces.
Put cheese slice on top of the bagel half; put apple slice on top of that and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Put in oven for 5 to 10 minutes at 350°.
But watch to make sure you don't burn it.
It's done when cheese starts to bubble.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix ingredients together; cook 1 1/2 hours over medium heat in a heavy saucepan or in the oven.

title: chocolate chip-date cake
directions: Combine dates, baking soda and boiling water, set aside.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Cream sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix well.
Add flour mixture and date mixture alternately to creamed ingredients.
Blend well. Spread in greased and floured 9 x 12-inch pan.
Sprinkle on top of batter the nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
No frosting needed.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pour boiling water over cabbage leaves, let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Season meat.
Add onion, rice and eggs.
Roll a portion of filling into each leaf.
Fasten ends with toothpicks. Place the cabbage rolls on rack.
Pour tomato soup and water over cabbage roll.
Cover and cook.

title: cheese dip
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage; drain excess grease.
Add Ro-Tel and chunks of Velveeta.
Cook until cheese is melted. Serve over baked potatoes or as dip.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle one side of meat with 1/2 of flour and pound in.
Turn meat and repeat with remaining flour.
Cut meat into 6 pieces.
Brown meat in Crisco in heavy skillet.
Cover tightly and simmer about 1 hour.
Add water, if needed.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Cover and simmer about 30 minutes or until tender.
Good over rice or potatoes.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Thaw bread approximately 5 to 6 hours.
Grease loaves and baking sheet with shortening.
Roll bread to rectangle approximately 8 x 12-inch.
Brush with egg mixture.
Cover with layer of pepperoni, then layer of cheese.
Roll like jelly roll, brushing with egg after each roll.
Pinch edges and seams closed. Brush with egg.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: italian zucchini crescent pie
directions: Separate crescent rolls.
Press into ungreased 10-inch pie pan, over bottom and up sides.
Spread crust with mustard.

title: bok choy with oyster sauce
directions: Boil water with sugar, salt, cornstarch and cooking oil, stirring until the sauce is a little thick.
Add oyster sauce. Blanch bok choy.
When it turns green, drain and put on a platter. Pour the sauce over the bok choy.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on a cookie sheet, covering bottom and halfway up sides to form a rim.
Bake 11 minutes at 375°.
Put on shelf in middle of oven.
Cool.

title: chicken fricassee with dumplings(a la muggs)
directions: Mix Bisquick, salt, paprika and pepper in plastic bag and shake chicken pieces.
Fry chicken in shortening until brown. Drain fat from pan.
Stir soup and milk into pan and scrape up chicken bits.
Return chicken to pan and bring to a simmer.
Mix dumplings and drop by teaspoonful on top of chicken and soup mixture.
Cover tightly and steam for 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Debone chicken and break into small pieces.
Place chicken in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread vegetables on top.
Mix the soups together and spread over top.
Pour broth over this.
In a bowl, add self-rising flour, milk and melted margarine.
Mix together until smooth.
Pour over chicken mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: In heated pan brown meat, pepper and onions.
Drain excess oil.
Add bay leaf and next 8 ingredients.
Cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer mixture about one hour.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Grease and flour three 1 pound coffee cans.
In a large bowl, beat eggs; add oil and water.
Stir in sugar and pumpkin.
Sift together flour, soda and seasonings and add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into prepared coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool on rack at least 10 minutes before removing from cans.

title: crab cakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into patties.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: golden pumpkin pickles
directions: Tie spices in cheesecloth.*
Combine sugar and vinegar in a large pot.
Add spice bag.
Bring to a boil.
Add pumpkin cubes and cook until fork-tender.
Remove spice bag and spoon into hot sterile jar.
Cover with syrup.
Seal at once.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine

pumpkin, eggs, cinnamon, brown sugar and evaporated milk. Pour over cake mixture in pan. Mix sugar, dry cake mix and margarine until crumbly. Sprinkle over pumpkin mixture. Sprinkle on 1 cup chopped pecans. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: toll house pie
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. In a large bowl, beat eggs until frothy, foamy and thick.
Beat in flour, sugar and brown sugar until blended.
Blend in melted butter.
Stir in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour in pie shell and bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Remove from oven.
Serve warm with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chicken curry over rice
directions: Saute the first 8 ingredients.
Add the mushroom soup plus water plus the liquid from beans.
Simmer.
Add almonds and serve over rice.
Top with dry Chinese noodles.

title: almond bark candy
directions: Place saltines in a pan side by side; melt margarine and brown sugar together.
Pour over saltines and bake 12 minutes at 350°. When cool, melt almond bark and pour over saltines.
Sprinkle crushed nuts over that.
Cool, break apart and eat.
They're great!

title: chicken breasts with garlic-vinegar sauce
directions: Sprinkle chicken lightly with salt and pepper.
Heat olive oil in large skillet.
Arrange chicken in pan, skin side down.
Cook over medium-high heat for 10 minutes, turning after 5 minutes to brown chicken on both sides.
Remove chicken with tongs and pour off all but 2 tablespoons of drippings.

Add garlic and rosemary to pan, reduce heat to medium-low and cook, stirring for 1 minute. Pour in vinegar and cook, stirring with wooden spoon for 2 minutes. Add stewed tomatoes, breaking up with side of spoon if pieces are large.
Place chicken in sauce, skin side up, and cook, partially covered, over low heat for 8 minutes.
Uncover and simmer for 5 to 8 more minutes, until chicken tests done and sauce is slightly reduced and thickened.
Spoon off any excess fat that has risen to surface.
The chicken may be made ahead to this point.
Bit by bit stir optional butter into sauce.
Taste for seasonings, adding more salt and pepper, if needed, before serving.
Yields 4 servings.

title: saucy oven spareribs
directions: Cut ribs into
serving	pieces.
Cook ribs in oil until browned on both sides;
sprinkle with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Place
spareribs in baking pan.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Bring sauce to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for about
10 minutes.
Pour over ribs.
Cover and bake at 325° for about
hours
or
until well done.
Uncover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: peach marshmallow salad
directions: Soak 1/2 pound small marshmallows and small can crushed pineapple with syrup together for one hour.
Add regular 2 cups sliced drained peaches.
Whip 1/2 pint whipping cream or you can use Cool Whip.
Add this with 1/2 pint mayonnaise.
Combine ingredients and freeze.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together eggs, oil, sugar, lemon juice and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add to first mixture.
Add apples and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in greased and floured pan (9 x 13-inch for 35 minutes or Bundt for 1 hour and 15 minutes) at 350°.

title: mustard beans
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, mustard, onion, salt and 1/3 cup water.
Bring mixture to boil, stirring until dissolved. Add drained beans.
Simmer, uncovered, for 5 minutes.
Allow to cool, cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
May substitute 1 pound cooked fresh wax beans.
Recipe is from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: shoo-fly cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients like pie dough; take out 1 1/2 cups crumbs for later.
In a large bowl, put the molasses and soda.
Gradually add boiling water.
Put into a
long, non-greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put the crumbs you saved on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter a casserole dish and line with broccoli. Place chicken on top.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: In saucepan mix sugar and cold water in saucepan.
Cook over boiling water in double boiler.
In small bowl mix together cornstarch and 1/4 cup cold water; stir into hot mixture and cook until thick.
Separate eggs; beat yolks slightly and stir into hot mixture.
Cook on low heat, do not scorch.
Cook about one minute. Add juice and rind of one lemon.
Add 2 tablespoons butter or margarine.
Cool.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Top with meringue (used from from whites of eggs separated).
Meringue is beaten until stiff.
Add a little sugar to taste and a teaspoon of vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Best ever!

title: potato soup
directions: Chop carrot, onion and potatoes and place in saucepan.
Boil until tender.
Add milk and butter; return to boil.
Simmer for about 20 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: mustard pickles
directions: Combine last 4 ingredients.
Heat to a boil.
Add pickles and reheat to a boil.
Bottle quickly and seal.
Invert jar until cool.

title: kiev style beef tenderloin
directions: Remove all fat and skin from meat. Cut in 1/2 x 2 inch strips. Sprinkle lightly with salt and pepper, let stand at room temperature for about 1 hour. Saute 2 tsp onion and mushrooms in 3 Tbsp butter until slightly browned. Sprinkle with flour and mix thoroughly.
Add beef broth, mustard and sour cream; stir to blend. Bring to boil. Season sauce to taste with salt and pepper, simmer 10 minutes.
Melt 3 Tbsp butter in skillet; quickly brown meat strips along with 1 tsp grated onion.
Add meat to sauce. Cover, keep hot for 20 minutes to blend flavors. Do not boil or simmer.
When ready to serve, heat quickly over direct heat. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: mama sisti's sunday meat sauce with pasta
directions: In an 8-quart pot, crush tomatoes by hand, removing bay leaf from can.
Add tomato paste; bring to boil.
Add oregano, parsley and wine.
Boil until wine aroma is gone.
Simmer 4 hours, covered, stirring every 15 minutes.
While sauce is cooking, fry beef and pork over high heat, searing all sides.
After meat is cooked, deglaze frying pan with red wine and balance of garlic.
Add drippings from frying pan to sauce.
Add beef and pork; continue to simmer for balance of 4 hours.
Serve over pasta with grated Locatelli.
Before serving, remove meat from sauce and serve separately.
Serve with Brollio Chianti or Monticello Pinot Noir.

title: nacho dip
directions: Scramble and brown hamburger; drain off excess fat.
Combine hamburger and both soups; heat on medium heat until heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: fettucini alfredo
directions: Melt oleo and cream cheese.
Add Parmesan cheese and milk. Cook until all is blended.
(May need extra milk to get desired consistency for sauce.)

title: blueberry cake roll
directions: Mix together the flour, margarine and pecans and pat into pan or dish.
Bake for 10 or 15 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool and chill.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Add cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; chill.

title: karen's low-fat chili
directions: Brown turkey in large pot in 1 tablespoon oil along with onion and celery.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir well.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel sauce
directions: Melt butter in heavy 2-quart pan. Stir in sugar, syrup, vanilla
and
salt.
Heat
to
boiling. Reduce heat;
simmer 5 minutes,
stirring	constantly.
Gradually stir in cream; heat to boiling. Stir constantly.
Remove from heat. Serve warm or cool. Makes 2 cups.

title: rice krispie easter eggs
directions: Mix peanut butter, oleo and 10x sugar first.
Then add Rice Krispies.
Shape in eggs and coat with chocolate.
Makes 25 eggs.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornmeal and flour.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after adding each.
Stir in butter, milk, lemon juice and rind.
Mix well.
Pour mixture into unbaked pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: golden cream soup
directions: Simmer vegetables and seasonings 15-20 min. Until tender. Blend milk and flour. Mix in vegetables and simmer until thickened. Add cheese and stir until melted.

title: mexican dip
directions: Layer the bottom of a square glass baking dish with the cream cheese.
Spread the chili over the cream cheese; top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Microwave on High until cheese is melted.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well.
Serve with bananas, apples, pineapple, strawberries, grapes, kiwi, etc.

title: salad dressing
directions: * Use blender for onion.

title: american chop suey(this is my own recipe.)
directions: Lightly brown hamburger, mushrooms and onion all together. Add celery which has been cooked in 1 1/2 cups water for 10 minutes.
Add this to hamburger and let simmer for 15 minutes. Stir now and then.
May need little more water.
Add the bean sprouts which have been drained.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine flour, soda and sugar.
Cut in shortening.
Add yeast and buttermilk.
Mix with spoon or hands until dough is formed. May be made into biscuits immediately or kept in the refrigerator for as long as two weeks.
Pinch off as needed and make into biscuits.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.

title: baked corn
directions: Beat the softened oleo, eggs and sour cream together.
Mix the cans of corn and muffin mix together and then add to the first mixture.
Pour into either a lightly greased 2-quart casserole dish
or two 1-quart casserole dishes.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine in large bowl shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 1 1/2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl often.
Add milk to sugar mixture.
Add sifted dry ingredients to sugar mixture alternately with bananas at slow speed for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Top with Banana Cream Frosting.

title: soft pretzels(makes 16 pretzels)
directions: Cover dough and thaw overnight in refrigerator or for several hours at room temperature until soft enough to shape.
On a floured surface, cut dough the long way into 8 strips.
Cover and let rise 10 minutes.
Roll each strip on a floured surface until 1/2 inch thick and 18 to 20 inches long.
Cut each strip in half and twist into pretzel shape.
Place on a nonstick sprayed baking sheet.
Brush with lukewarm water.
Sprinkle with poppy or sesame seed.
Let rise, uncovered , for 15 to 20 minutes.
Place a shallow pan of hot water on bottom shelf of preheated oven.
Bake pretzels on middle shelf at 425° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Cream the brown sugar, peanut butter and oleo or butter; add and beat until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour mixture alternately with milk and sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 60 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Cool completely.

title: german cheese squares
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, line bottom of pan with 1 package of crescent rolls. Spread mixture on top of crescent rolls.
Place other crescent roll package on top of mixture. Beat egg white (until frothy) and brush on top of crescent rolls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and top with icing.

title: quick barbecue spareribs
directions: Place spareribs in crock-pot.
Add barbecue sauce and onion. Cook on high for 10 hours.

title: pam's brunch dish
directions: Mix together and pour into a greased oblong baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes or more (until done).
Let stand a few minutes before cutting to serve.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage, drain well.
Add peppers, onions and mushrooms and saute.
Combine tomato sauce, stewed tomatoes, tomato puree and spices.
Add to hamburger mixture and simmer several hours.

title: stuffed chicken breast
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add vegetables.
Saute until tender. Stir in 1/4 teaspoon of salt, 1/4 teaspoon black pepper, thyme and parsley; set aside.
Place each piece of chicken on individual pieces of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place 2 to 3 tablespoons of vegetable mix on each piece of chicken.
Fold chicken around mixture and secure with toothpick.
Pour 1 tablespoon cooking wine over each chicken piece.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Wrap chicken securely with foil.
Place on baking sheet. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: fiesta
directions: Brown ground beef with onions in skillet, stirring frequently. Add next 3 ingredients.
Simmer until thickened slightly.
Stir in 1/2 cup cheese.
Put in serving bowl and top with 1/2 cup sour cream.
Serve hot with tortilla chips, lettuce and tomatoes.

title: easy chuck roast
directions: Season roast.
Peel potatoes.
Layer in bottom of casserole dish.
Add carrots, onion, mushroom soup, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 5 to 6 hours at 200°.

title: copper carrots
directions: Slice carrots; cook until tender.
Let cool.
Chop onion and pepper; mix with carrots.

title: mom's banana bread
directions: *Sour milk with 4 teaspoons vinegar and let stand 5 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix ingredients together in the order they are listed.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Makes 1 (2 pound) loaf.
If making 1 pound loaves, bake for 50 minutes.
Makes 3 (1 pound) loaves.
The riper the bananas, the moister the bread.

title: lunch box tuna swirls
directions: In a bowl, combine tuna, mayonnaise, onion, relish, liquid smoke and lemon juice.
Cover and refrigerate.
In the morning, cut the crusts off the bread and flatten each slice with a rolling pin. Spread a thin layer of the tuna filling on the bread.
Lay the bread slices on a slightly dampened cloth and roll up as you would a jelly roll.
Seal each seam with a dab of butter.
The result is a tuna roll that looks much like a jelly roll.
Three will be plenty for most children under 13.

title: corn flake candy
directions: Combine corn syrup and sugar in sauce pan. Heat until almost a boil, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Spoon in peanut butter. Stir until smooth and creamy. Measure corn flakes into a large bowl. Pour corn syrup-sugar mixture over corn flakes. Fold together until all corn flakes are covered well. Pour into dish or tupperware container,
pressing lightly. Cut into squares.

title: hot mulled cider punch
directions: Combine cider, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Bring to a boil and cook 5 minutes.
Strain.
Serve hot.
Will make 48 punch cup servings.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake cornbread mix according to directions and crumble. Combine Ranch dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise in small bowl. In another bowl, mix together peppers, tomatoes, onions, beans and corn. In a 3-quart salad bowl, layer 1/2 of cornbread, 1/2 vegetables, 1/2 cheese, 1/2 bacon and 1/2 dressing.
